The paper deals with logical definability of graph spectra, which is a topic in both logic (cs.LO) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algebraic and combinatorial problems related to graph spectra, which are relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses techniques from computational geometry (cs.CG) to prove some of its results.
